00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:06.600
I want you to really notice two things

00:12:06.600 --> 00:12:10.520
within this thought tonight of the trip that Elijah takes.

00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:14.100
I want you to first consider with me the provision of God.

00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:20.360
I'm so thankful that our God is the God who provides.

00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:22.480
In fact, that'll be one of the names of God

00:12:23.320 --> 00:12:24.640
that we study on that Wednesday night series.

00:12:24.640 --> 00:12:27.120
He's the God who provides.

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.480
And we begin to think about our lives

00:12:29.480 --> 00:12:30.720
and we think about the provision,

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:33.000
and so often, when we consider provision,

00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:35.640
yes, we think about the things that we need,

00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:38.160
but you understand that Jesus says twice,

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:42.080
within just a few verses in the book of Matthew,

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:44.280
that God already knows, our Father knows

00:12:44.280 --> 00:12:45.960
what we have need of.

00:12:45.960 --> 00:12:47.880
We need not to be concerned of those things.

00:12:47.880 --> 00:12:50.200
God knows what we have need of.

00:12:50.200 --> 00:12:54.220
We understand that God is able to provide for us,

00:12:54.220 --> 00:12:56.840
that God is able to meet your needs

00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:58.600
and my needs and our needs,

00:12:58.600 --> 00:13:00.160
and we can rejoice in that,

00:13:00.160 --> 00:13:04.200
and we find that God is going to provide for his servant.

00:13:04.200 --> 00:13:06.760
Again, God knew exactly where Elijah was,

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:09.920
and God sent an angel in verse number five,

00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:12.080
and that angel touched Elijah.

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:13.800
When Elijah was in that low place,

00:13:13.800 --> 00:13:16.140
when Elijah said, take my life from me,

00:13:16.140 --> 00:13:18.160
when Elijah was in despair,

00:13:18.160 --> 00:13:21.120
God met him and God sent this angel

00:13:21.120 --> 00:13:24.060
and said unto him, arise and eat.

00:13:24.060 --> 00:13:25.480
Notice verse six, and he looked,

00:13:25.480 --> 00:13:28.000
and behold, there was a cake baking on the coals,

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:30.480
and a cruise of water at his head,

00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:32.040
and the Bible says that he didn't eat and drink

00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:33.920
and laid him down again.

00:13:33.920 --> 00:13:35.680
I mean, I'd be absolutely astonished,

00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:36.560
and where'd that come from?

00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:37.480
What's going on?

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:39.700
I mean, it's an amazing thing, is it not?

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:41.720
The way that God supernaturally,

00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:45.680
miraculously provided for his servant.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:46.880
That's our God.

00:13:46.880 --> 00:13:48.480
That's who we serve.

00:13:48.480 --> 00:13:50.800
Our God is a real God.

00:13:50.800 --> 00:13:53.320
Our God is a God who is able.

00:13:53.320 --> 00:13:54.640
You say, but I don't see how.

00:13:54.640 --> 00:13:57.200
You don't have to see how,

00:13:57.200 --> 00:14:01.520
because God works in the impossible situations.

00:14:01.520 --> 00:14:03.680
Because when we look at it and we say,

00:14:03.680 --> 00:14:05.640
there's no hope, it's impossible,

00:14:05.640 --> 00:14:09.680
that's really the time in which God is ready to work.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:14.120
For with our God, nothing is impossible.

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:16.480
Aren't you thankful for that truth?

00:14:16.480 --> 00:14:18.880
We find this evening that he laid down again,

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:20.400
according to the end of verse number six,

00:14:20.400 --> 00:14:22.560
and the angel of the Lord in verse seven

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:24.400
came again the second time and touched him

00:14:24.400 --> 00:14:25.740
and said, arise and eat,

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:29.440
because the journey is too great for thee.

00:14:29.440 --> 00:14:31.200
And he rose and did eat and drink

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:33.520
and went in the strength of that meat

00:14:33.520 --> 00:14:36.920
40 days and 40 nights into Horeb, the mount of God.

00:14:36.920 --> 00:14:39.280
What a meal it must have been.

00:14:39.280 --> 00:14:40.280
Amen?

00:14:40.280 --> 00:14:42.440
There is nothing that I have ever consumed

00:14:42.440 --> 00:14:45.040
that kept me for 40 days and 40 nights.

00:14:45.040 --> 00:14:47.000
And I'm guessing it's not anything

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:49.080
that you've ever consumed either, amen?

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:51.360
And the reality is that we ate lunch

00:14:51.360 --> 00:14:53.260
and in a little while we'll be ready for dinner.

00:14:53.260 --> 00:14:55.300
And that's just how it works.

00:14:55.300 --> 00:15:00.080
And here we find that God provides.

00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:04.040
Just rejoice for a moment this evening that God provides.

00:15:05.160 --> 00:15:06.400
He's a good God.

00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:10.640
The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:15.640
He leads us, He provides for us.

00:15:17.760 --> 00:15:21.240
As a good shepherd, the shepherd knows the needs

00:15:21.240 --> 00:15:22.080
of the sheep.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.480
Our God knows what we need.

00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:27.760
And He provides what we need.

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:30.120
It may not always be the way that we think

00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:33.160
or what we might figure that it should be,

00:15:33.160 --> 00:15:36.160
but God always provides.

00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:38.640
He's a good God, He's a gracious God.

00:15:39.560 --> 00:15:42.600
But I notice in this trip that Elijah takes

00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:45.000
when he's fleeing for his life

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:47.120
that there's not just the provision of God,

00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:49.640
but I also want us to consider this evening

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:51.780
the probing of God.

00:15:51.780 --> 00:15:52.620
The probing of God.

00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:53.880
Have you ever been asked a question

00:15:53.880 --> 00:15:56.480
that's a probing question?

00:15:56.480 --> 00:16:00.540
A question that requires you to do some soul searching?

00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:03.640
In fact, I believe this evening that really

00:16:03.640 --> 00:16:06.640
the question of that first song that we sang this evening

00:16:06.640 --> 00:16:07.820
is such a question.

00:16:07.820 --> 00:16:11.940
I wonder, have I done my best for Jesus?

00:16:13.140 --> 00:16:15.640
Every time I sing that song, it convicts me.

00:16:19.060 --> 00:16:20.940
He is worthy of our best.

00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:26.000
Not just good enough, not just get by,

00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:27.900
but He's worthy of our best.

00:16:27.900 --> 00:16:30.660
We're working for the master, the king of the universe.

00:16:31.580 --> 00:16:34.500
And here, there's a probing question.

00:16:34.500 --> 00:16:37.900
We've used it for the title of our message this evening,

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:40.060
but we find that in verse nine,

00:16:40.060 --> 00:16:42.100
the Bible says he came thither into a cave

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:44.260
and lodged there, and behold,

00:16:44.260 --> 00:16:45.820
the word of the Lord came to him,

00:16:45.820 --> 00:16:50.280
and he said unto him, what doest thou hear, Elijah?

00:16:51.180 --> 00:16:53.320
You understand how that's a probing question?

00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:54.220
Could I phrase it this way,

00:16:54.220 --> 00:16:55.820
maybe a way that we might use it today?

00:16:55.820 --> 00:16:57.020
What are you doing here?

00:16:57.940 --> 00:16:59.140
What are you doing here?

00:17:00.100 --> 00:17:01.140
Why are you here?

00:17:02.100 --> 00:17:06.020
Elijah gives an answer in verse 10,

00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:09.300
and he says this, I have been very jealous

00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:10.780
for the Lord God of hosts,

00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:13.260
for the children of Israel have forsaken thy covenant.

00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:15.320
They've thrown down thine altars

00:17:15.320 --> 00:17:17.700
and slain thy prophets with the sword,

00:17:17.700 --> 00:17:20.140
and I, even I only, am left,

00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:22.920
and they seek my life to take it away.

00:17:22.920 --> 00:17:25.860
Elijah understood the circumstances,

00:17:25.860 --> 00:17:27.620
the conditions in Israel,

00:17:27.620 --> 00:17:30.300
and that which he was, and how he was serving the Lord.

00:17:30.300 --> 00:17:32.060
He was wrong on his assessment

00:17:32.060 --> 00:17:33.820
that he was the only one remaining,

00:17:33.820 --> 00:17:35.700
and we'll see that at the end of the text,

00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:39.520
but we find that he was, he gave an answer,

00:17:39.520 --> 00:17:41.700
but I wanna, I would submit to you this evening

00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:43.680
that as you look at the continuation

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:45.160
of the text of Scripture,

00:17:45.160 --> 00:17:47.400
that it was probably not satisfactory.

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:48.240
Why?

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:49.060
Because in verse number 11,

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:49.900
the Bible says, and he said,

00:17:49.900 --> 00:17:52.340
go forth and stand upon the mount before the Lord,

00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:55.660
and behold, the Lord passed by in a great and strong wind,

00:17:55.660 --> 00:17:57.860
rent the mountains and break in pieces

00:17:57.860 --> 00:17:59.420
the rocks before the Lord,

00:17:59.420 --> 00:18:00.860
but the Lord was not in the wind,

00:18:00.860 --> 00:18:02.180
and after the wind, an earthquake,

00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:03.500
but the Lord was not in the earthquake,

00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:05.360
and after the earthquake, a fire,

00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:06.580
but the Lord was not in the fire,

00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:07.420
and after the fire,

00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:09.760
notice what it says, a still, small voice.

00:18:10.900 --> 00:18:13.980
We've often spoken about that still, small voice.

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:17.500
We find that the Bible says that it was so

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:19.480
that when Elijah heard it,

00:18:19.480 --> 00:18:23.300
can I pause just for a moment and ask the question,

00:18:23.300 --> 00:18:25.260
do you hear the voice of God?

00:18:25.260 --> 00:18:26.560
I don't mean audibly,

00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:30.520
but I mean, do you hear from God when he's speaking to you?

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:35.640
Do you have a ear that is sensitive

00:18:35.640 --> 00:18:37.119
to the voice of the Lord?

00:18:38.040 --> 00:18:39.440
You know, it's amazing how many times

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:40.340
throughout the Scriptures,

00:18:40.340 --> 00:18:43.760
you'll find the phraseology of hear.

00:18:44.679 --> 00:18:47.900
Let him that hath ears hear.

00:18:49.280 --> 00:18:50.520
And we find this evening,

00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:53.600
the Bible says that when Elijah heard it,

00:18:55.040 --> 00:18:56.400
sometimes there's noise,

00:18:57.239 --> 00:18:59.960
just background noise, right?

00:18:59.960 --> 00:19:02.440
And it might not have your attention,

00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:06.440
but then you hear somebody's voice that you know,

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:08.200
maybe your spouse, maybe a child,

00:19:08.200 --> 00:19:10.440
maybe a parent for a child.

00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:12.880
You hear that voice, and it gets your attention, why?

00:19:12.880 --> 00:19:17.280
Because you're sensitive to the voice of that individual.

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:19.320
Does that make sense tonight?

00:19:19.320 --> 00:19:21.280
We know the voices of people,

00:19:21.280 --> 00:19:23.140
no doubt this evening,

00:19:23.140 --> 00:19:25.619
if you were to be in a crowd of people,

00:19:25.980 --> 00:19:28.340
and if you have a spouse here this evening,

00:19:28.340 --> 00:19:30.260
if you have a child here this evening,

00:19:30.260 --> 00:19:31.940
and you heard them call out,

00:19:31.940 --> 00:19:35.020
if you had a friend, a parent that you knew very well,

00:19:35.020 --> 00:19:37.179
and you heard them cry out your name,

00:19:37.179 --> 00:19:40.220
you're familiar with their voice.

00:19:40.220 --> 00:19:41.500
You hear it.

00:19:41.500 --> 00:19:43.600
Listen, we ought to know the voice of God.

00:19:44.679 --> 00:19:46.739
We ought to long to hear from God.

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:48.940
We come to church,

00:19:48.940 --> 00:19:51.940
we don't come just for a social gathering.

00:19:51.940 --> 00:19:53.739
We read our Bibles on a daily basis,

00:19:53.739 --> 00:19:54.940
we don't just read our Bibles

00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:59.940
to check a box in a Bible reading schedule plan, no.

00:19:59.940 --> 00:20:04.320
and we come to church so we can hear from God.

00:20:04.320 --> 00:20:05.780
Because this is the amazing thing,

00:20:05.780 --> 00:20:09.080
the God of the universe wants to talk to us.

00:20:09.080 --> 00:20:10.780
He has a message for us.

00:20:10.780 --> 00:20:14.860
Listen, of all the 7,000 that had not bowed the knee

00:20:14.860 --> 00:20:16.240
according to what God said,

00:20:16.240 --> 00:20:21.620
in this chapter, He's focused on one, Elijah.

00:20:21.620 --> 00:20:26.080
And He's speaking to one, Elijah.

00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:28.240
And what a joy to know that our God loves us

00:20:28.240 --> 00:20:29.160
and He cares about us

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:31.840
and He wants to speak to us.

00:20:31.840 --> 00:20:36.040
And I wonder tonight, are we listening for the voice of God?

00:20:36.040 --> 00:20:38.280
Are we hearing the voice of God?

00:20:39.480 --> 00:20:43.160
Are we responding to the voice of God?

00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:47.200
You ever find someone that's good at ignoring?

00:20:47.200 --> 00:20:49.000
I mean, like, you know they heard you.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:52.300
Men, oftentimes, we get accused of having selective hearing.

00:20:53.680 --> 00:20:54.720
Amen?

00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:56.240
He says he needs hearing aids.

00:20:56.240 --> 00:20:58.560
He don't need hearing aids, he just has selective hearing.

00:20:58.560 --> 00:21:01.080
He's not hard of hearing, he just has selective hearing.

00:21:01.080 --> 00:21:03.120
And all the women said, praise the Lord, Pastor,

00:21:03.120 --> 00:21:05.120
thank you for helping us out, amen?

00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:08.440
But the reality is that sometimes we have that select,

00:21:08.440 --> 00:21:11.120
listen, Nova is one.

00:21:11.120 --> 00:21:12.360
Can she ignore?

00:21:12.360 --> 00:21:15.080
Holy cow, that girl can ignore.

00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:20.080
You're like, hey, Nova, Nova.

00:21:20.080 --> 00:21:22.040
And man, she ain't paying no kind of attention to you.

00:21:22.040 --> 00:21:25.080
She can ignore you and ignore you.

00:21:25.080 --> 00:21:27.760
Listen, that's not how we should be with the voice of God.

00:21:28.920 --> 00:21:30.440
We ought to be sensitive.

00:21:31.360 --> 00:21:33.200
We ought to be ready to hear it,

00:21:33.200 --> 00:21:35.920
longing to hear the voice of God

00:21:37.080 --> 00:21:40.760
and responding in obedience to the voice of God.

00:21:40.760 --> 00:21:42.400
It says when Elijah heard it,

00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:45.800
that he wrapped his face in his mantle

00:21:45.800 --> 00:21:48.639
and he went out and stood in the entering of the cave.

00:21:51.880 --> 00:21:54.360
Some people are looking for some big things.

00:21:55.319 --> 00:22:00.319
The strong wind, the earthquake, and the fire,

00:22:01.279 --> 00:22:03.800
they really didn't impact Elijah.

00:22:03.800 --> 00:22:06.639
We know the still, small voice of God.

00:22:06.639 --> 00:22:07.800
It calls him to go out.

00:22:08.839 --> 00:22:10.479
And he wrapped himself in his mantle

00:22:10.479 --> 00:22:12.320
and he went out and stood in the entering of the cave.

00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:13.639
And the Bible says,

00:22:13.639 --> 00:22:16.199
behold, there came a voice unto him and said,

00:22:17.279 --> 00:22:21.160
what doest thou hear, Elijah?

00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:23.800
Now, if I could make the illustration this evening,

00:22:24.160 --> 00:22:26.040
God is our heavenly father.

00:22:26.040 --> 00:22:27.919
Do we agree with that?

00:22:27.919 --> 00:22:29.000
We are his children.

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:31.600
If you're saved this evening, you're a child of God.

00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:33.279
You were born in the family of God

00:22:33.279 --> 00:22:34.760
and he became our father.

00:22:34.760 --> 00:22:36.960
And what a joy that is.

00:22:36.960 --> 00:22:39.880
And I understand that as we study the scriptures

00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:42.160
and we get the opportunity to see the truth

00:22:42.160 --> 00:22:44.600
of how he deals with us as his children,

00:22:44.600 --> 00:22:47.320
he disciplines us and he corrects us.

00:22:47.320 --> 00:22:48.800
He loves us.

00:22:48.800 --> 00:22:50.080
There's so many things that he does.

00:22:50.080 --> 00:22:52.119
But I look at this passage of scripture

00:22:52.119 --> 00:22:55.199
and I'm reminded of how a father might behave

00:22:55.199 --> 00:22:56.720
and interact with their children.

00:22:56.720 --> 00:22:58.320
Have you ever, maybe a parent,

00:22:58.320 --> 00:23:01.279
and I'll understand that God is our father,

00:23:01.279 --> 00:23:03.040
but as a parent this evening,

00:23:03.040 --> 00:23:05.119
